The paper discusses a problem in computer vision (recovering intrinsic data structure from corrupted observations) and proposes a novel algorithm for solving it. The paper also mentions that the proposed algorithm has applications in large scale computer vision problems, indicating that it may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The algorithm involves minimizing a combination of nuclear norm and $l_1$ norm, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The algorithm has a low computational complexity and is highly parallelizable, which suggests that it may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
